&lt;h2 data-section-id=&quot;lu8iu7&quot; data-start=&quot;756&quot; data-end=&quot;792&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Start Your Adventure at Via Logic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Duration&lt;/strong&gt;: Full-time, W2 position&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary: &lt;/strong&gt;$60,000-100,000 annually&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience Required&lt;/strong&gt;: 5+ years&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 10pt;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;While this role is primarily remote, candidates must reside within a reasonable commuting distance of Alexandria, VA and be available to attend occasional in-person meetings, team events, customer engagements, and other business activities as needed.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Route Into Business Ops&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;328&quot; data-end=&quot;601&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;At Via Logic, we&#39;re a growing government contracting company, which means this role is a little bit of everything - but first and foremost, we&#39;re looking for someone who understands how to keep the operational, financial, and compliance side of the business running smoothly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;603&quot; data-end=&quot;1152&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;As a Business Operations Specialist, you&#39;ll support finance administration, government contracting operations, compliance activities, people operations, and internal business processes. One day you may be helping track contract-related documentation, expense reimbursements, or invoices; the next you may be coordinating onboarding activities, supporting recruiting efforts, or helping improve an internal process. If you&#39;re organized, resourceful, detail-oriented, and enjoy wearing multiple hats in a growing business, you&#39;ll thrive in this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;line-height: 1.4;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 14pt; font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Mission&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 data-section-id=&quot;31gd69&quot; data-start=&quot;237&quot; data-end=&quot;293&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Government Contracting, Finance &amp;amp; Compliance Support&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;295&quot; data-end=&quot;1001&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Support day-to-day government contracting operations by maintaining contract-related documentation, trackers, and records; assisting with compliance activities; and helping ensure alignment with customer, company, and regulatory requirements. Review contract documents, FAR clauses, flowdowns, modifications, and other contractual requirements to identify obligations, support internal implementation, and help maintain compliance. Assist with finance-related administrative activities, including invoice coordination, expense reimbursements, reporting, and operational recordkeeping. Help ensure business records remain organized, accurate, audit-ready, and aligned with company and customer expectations.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 data-section-id=&quot;263ieh&quot; data-start=&quot;1706&quot; data-end=&quot;1737&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif;&quot;&gt;Business Operations Support&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p data-start=&quot;1739&

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Type:&lt;/strong&gt; Full-time Employee (W-2) position&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Experience:&lt;/strong&gt; Minimum of 10+ years of relevant technical experience.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Residence:&lt;/strong&gt; Current U.S. residence and within U.S for 3 of the past 5 years.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location:&lt;/strong&gt; 100% United States (U.S.) Based Remote with ALL being performed within the U.S. &lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trail Pass: &lt;/strong&gt;U.S. Citizenship required to obtain a Public Trust clearance.&lt;br&gt;&lt;em&gt;**Please note: U.S. citizenship is someone who was born in the US or obtained citizenship through naturalization that the government will verify. The government has excluded non-citizen nationals, lawful permanent residents (green card holders), refugees, or those on temporary visas&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Us: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;Via Logic LLC is an information technology partner supporting mission-driven work across DevSecOps, cloud engineering, data science, cybersecurity, and national security analytics. Our team includes engineers, developers, architects, and problem-solvers who work alongside federal partners such as DHS, DOJ, and DOD, as well as select commercial clients, to deliver solutions that matter.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We focus on modernizing complex environments by automating infrastructure, improving security, enabling cloud-native operations, applying DevSecOps practices, and helping organizations make smarter use of their data. Our work spans everything from enterprise architecture to AI/ML implementations and identity management, giving our clients practical solutions and clear paths forward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We also put a lot of care into how we work. Via Logic values flexibility, collaboration, and a people-first culture that supports work-life balance and gives our team the space to do meaningful, high-impact work—wherever mission needs take us.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;We’re looking for an immensely talented Solution Architect to join our growing team! This architect will have advanced expertise in cloud architecture, data analytics, data modeling, machine learning, security, and emerging cloud-native technologies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a key member of our team, you will support product teams in migrating, modernizing, automating, and innovating applications. The role demands strong technical skills to architect, design, develop, and engineer complex projects that deliver business value and strategic insights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;**Candidates must meet public trust clearance requirements&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Basic Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: Bachelor’s degree or higher in Computer Science, Data Science, Statistics, Mathematics, Engineering, or a related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 11 years of relevant experience in enterprise software architecture, analytics, machine learning, artificial intelligence or a similar role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record of delivering impactful emerging technology value including AI/ML/NLP innovations and data-driven solutions in a cloud native environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;MUST BE A U.S. CITIZEN AND RESIDE IN THE U.S. All work must be performed in the U.S.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Department of Homeland Security (DHS) Public Trust U.S. citizenship is mandatory, as this work is for a federal government client. Candidates will need to successfully complete a Background Investigation (BI) and credit check prior to beginning work. Nothing in applicants’ history should prevent them from obtaining a public trust security clearance.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
